The paper proposes a novel semantics for declarative specifications of domain-specific heuristics in Answer Set Programming (ASP), which is a subfield of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of negation as failure and aggregates in heuristic conditions, which are topics related to Logic (cs.LO) and Programming Languages (cs.PL). The paper deals with combinatorial problems, which are often studied in the subfield of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM). Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
